    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved shallot</strong> and <strong>peeled garlic</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>chopped green chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>creamed coconut</strong>,<strong> basil</strong>,<strong> </strong>the<strong> </strong>juice of your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, <strong>fish sauce</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>roasted peanuts </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and 1 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 1/2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> Thai green curry pesto</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a food processor? Finely chop the ingredients and grind in a pestle & mortar instead!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
